<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-40-0383 </DOCNO><TEXT>The operation of the Bulk Electricity System (BES) to certain predefinedlevels of security has become increasingly difficult as the system hasgrown in complexity and a greater number of constraints and limits havebeen applied to the operating environment. Consequently, a number ofaids for emergency control of the BES have been developed and installedover the years. Specifically, these aids for emergency control have beenimplemented in order to prevent system disturbances, contain system disturbances,and minimize the effect of system disturbances on customers.</TEXT></DOC>